    {
      "id": "32aeea50_1caca77c",
      "file_path": "applications/common/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdp/xacml/application/common/matchable/MatchablePolicyType.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 60,
      "message": "I was thinking just put MatchablePropertyTypeString::new, etc., into the map values.  Then the construction of the map would be much cleaner.  In fact, could probably use Map.of() then:\n\n  Map<String,Function<ToscaProperty,MatchablePropertyTypeBase>> map = Map.of(\n    TOSCA_PRIMITIVE_STRING, MatchablePropertyTypeString::new,\n    ...\n    );\n\nAll of this assumes that java will match the correct \"new\" operator; it may have a problem since there is a new(ToscaPolicy) and a new(ToscaSchemaEntity), but I THINK it will work.  If not, then I'd probably just put it back the way it was.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-03-18 21:23:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "aede6ee5_a3fc867d",
      "file_path": "applications/common/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdp/xacml/application/common/matchable/MatchablePolicyType.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 171,
      "message": "with the changes I suggested above, this would be:\n\n  return new MatchableProperty(property, construct.apply(toscaProperty));\n\nThe map MAY be faster since it computes a hash and finds it rather than potentially doing multiple comparisons.  If there were only 2-3 of these, then I would have left it as was, but with this many items, makes more sense to put the \"different\" parts into a map, while keeping the common stuff (i.e., new MatchableProperty()) in one place.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-03-18 21:23:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "96a99845_7e818516",
      "file_path": "applications/common/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdp/xacml/application/common/matchable/MatchablePropertyTypeInteger.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 51,
      "message": "Since an \"Integer\" is needed rather than an \"int\", valueOf() should be used.  The reason is that parseInt() returns an \"int\" which then has to be autoboxed into an Integer, whereas valueOf() will return the Integer directly, skipping the autoboxing (in this code, at least)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-03-18 21:23:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "46fafe61_b5c07b67",
      "unresolved": true
    },
